parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become disengaged, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch or release properly
the plastic cover on the buckle breaks
the seat belt does not stay connected
the seat belt fails to latch or unlatch

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood and hatch dampers can cause the hood or hatch to suddenly fall, potentially causing injury or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The hood or hatch does not stay in the up position
the hood or hatch falls suddenly
the hood or hatch is difficult to hold up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel tilt mechanism can cause the ignition to shut off while turning the steering wheel, resulting in a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel tilt falls apart while driving
the bolt or nut on the tilt steering wheel becomes loose
the ignition shuts off while turning the steering wheel
